               <head>Abu'l-Fazl, correspondence</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100074 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85104368 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85077509" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_70x-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Unidentified collection of correspondence attributed to <persName key="person_f7577" role="att">Shaykh Abū al-Faz̤l Nāgawrī</persName> in the colophon 
                        </p>
                        <p>Internal references suggest some of the contents dates from the reign of the Timurid or Mughal <persName key="viaf_3264079" role="oth">Emperor Akbar I </persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning 
</p>
                        <p>No rubrication or rulings </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 48v): completed by <persName key="person_f7093" role="scr">Bhedi La‘l</persName> or <persName key="person_f7093" role="scr">Phande La‘l</persName> (?) on 25 Jumādá al-Avval regnal year 7 of <persName key="viaf_308694679" role="oth">Emperor Akbar Shāh II</persName> (c. 26 May 1813)
                        </p>
                        <p>Heavily annotated in between lines and in margins in parts
</p>
                        <p>Papers alternate between orange and white
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
